  "title": "Site Engineer (Civil Engineering)",
  "description": "<p>In view of our recently awarded projects, we are looking to expand our engineering team.</p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop project plans, including timelines, resource requirements, and budgets.</li><li>Coordinate with stakeholders to ensure project objectives are clearly defined and met.</li><li>Monitor project progress and performance, identifying risks and implementing mitigation strategies.</li><li>Review and interpret engineering designs, drawings, and specifications.</li><li>Ensure compliance with regulatory standards, codes, and safety guidelines.</li><li>Conduct site inspections and quality control checks to verify work meets project requirements.</li><li>Foster a collaborative work environment, promoting communication and problem-solving.</li><li>Prepare progress reports, technical documentation, and project updates.</li><li>Address client concerns and inquiries promptly, ensuring high levels of satisfaction.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil/Structural Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>With an understanding of civil engineering principles, construction methodologies, and project management techniques.</li><li>Effective communication skills, both verbal and written, with the ability to liaise confidently with clients and stakeholders.</li></ul><p>The remuneration package shall be commensurate with relevant project experiences, proven track records and professional skills.</p>",
